dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of almost eighty-five thousand programs, each solving one of ten coding problems, covering a wide spectrum of difficulty levels from entry-level programming exercises to challenging algorithmic questions. The dataset was manually inspected and labeled by fourteen PhD students and exchange scholars at the University of California, Davis.
dcterms:title: DYPRO Dataset

dcterms:description: The Daikon system for dynamic detection of likely invariants, which proposes likely loop invariants in each loop of a program.
dcterms:title: Daikon Loop Invariants Dataset
